Deployment YAML in kubernetes

# kubectl delete all --all

# kubectl get pods

# kubectl create -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Sonal0409/DevOps-Training-March-26-Ericsson/refs/heads/master/kubernetesfiles/deployment.yml

# kubectl get all

Scale up or scale down pods

# kubectl scale deployment mydeploy --replicas=10

Scale down:

# kubectl scale deployment mydeploy --replicas=1

Create service to access form browser

# kubectl create -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Sonal0409/DevOps-Training-March-26-Ericsson/refs/heads/master/kubernetesfiles/service.yml

# kubectl get all

Go to browser and give url : 

localhost:30009

Now come back to terminal --> update Image 

kubectl set image deployment mydeploy c1=leaddevops/kubeserve:v2

# kubectl get deployment -o wide

# kubectl get pods

Refresh the browser-> you will see v2

Rollout undo of deployment:

# kubectl rollout undo deployment mydeploy

# kubectl get deployment -o wide

# kubectl get pods

Refresh the browser-> you will see v1














































































